column5: Dude intentionally went for a dip in Kempenfelt Bay today.  http://www.thebarrieexaminer.com/2016/04/15/taking-an-early-dip-in-kempenfelt-bay  Mine would never fall again.

Hell the sun was shining, good for him. When we lived up on Farlain Lake the old couple beside us use to be in the lake every weekend... during the winter! (just wish they hadn't made the run and back naked.... )

KBay is freezing in August!   We moved south from North Bay to Barrie in the summer when I was about 11. We'd been swimming in Nipissing for 4 months by then and ran right into Simcoe. Delayed my puberty by at least a year.

Peanuts grow in the ground.......not trees.........so you are RIGHT ! ! !  https://www.google.com/search?q=growing+peanuts&espv=2&biw=1067&bih=517&tbm=isch&tbo=u&source=univ&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjStdu_1pPMAhXCRiYKHUuNA4UQsAQINQ#imgrc=U-6GP3bOT0ztUM%3A
Peanuts are a legume, not a nut, I thought?

Heck I put the dock in this weekend, water went over my chest waders, I'm probably going to have to sit down to pee for another week, my best friend pulled a turtle and won't even stick his head out anymore  (Might even have to change my name to "Little Cliff")
